summary:
• Gas Supply Agreement: 7-year deal with GGNZ Ltd for up to 7PJ/year from 1 Oct 2025, extendable by 3 years.
  • Strategic Impact: Diversifies gas supply, reduces single-field reliance, supports transition to renewables.
  • Renewable Generation: Expected 200–300GWh/year from gas peaking units (98% renewable generation in normal hydrology).
  • Investment Focus: Over $2bn committed to renewable projects in past 4 years.
  • Net Zero Target: Generation operations net zero by 2035.

No material capital markets/trading actions (e.g., raising, halt, or key dates) identified.

Summary of Material Information:

  • Director Share Purchase: Hartley Atkinson (Director) acquired 200,000 AFT shares on-market at an average price of $2.83 per share (~$566,000 total).
  • Post-Transaction Holdings:
  • Atkinson Family Trust: Increased stake from 72,059,496 to 72,259,496 ordinary shares.
  • Personal Holdings: 867,826 ordinary shares (jointly held).
  • Timing: Transactions occurred 30-Jun, 1-Jul, and 2-Jul 2025; no closed-period breach reported.

No material impact on capital structure or liquidity identified.

Material Information Summary (ASX Announcement – Monthly Traffic Report & Media Updates)

Operational Highlights (May 2025)

  • Capacity decline: Group ASKs down 2.7% YoY (Long Haul -2.2%, Domestic -5.5%, Short Haul International -2.2%) due to engine maintenance delays.
  • Yield improvement: Group YTD underlying RASK up 2.0% YoY (Long Haul +2.8%, Short Haul +0.4%).
  • Load factor: 82.0% (May) and 83.5% (YTD), up 2.5ppt and 1.9ppt YoY, respectively.

Fleet/Network Expansion (Media Releases)

  1. Tasman/Pacific capacity boost: 1.7M seats (+8% premium) added for summer 2025–26; includes 130K extra Tasman seats and 25K Pacific seats.
  2. China tourism joint venture: $700K marketing investment with Air China/Tourism NZ to stimulate inbound travel; Shanghai-Auckland premium seats +33%.
  3. North America expansion: 34K additional seats (+8% YoY); premium seats up 20.5K (e.g., LAX +16% capacity, Houston/Vancouver boosts).
  4. New routes:
  5. Christchurch–Adelaide (seasonal, 15K seats from Oct 2025).
  6. A321neo fleet additions: Two new aircraft (70K annual seats).

Key Dates

  • A321neo delivery: First aircraft entered service June 2025; second due late June.

Format: Concise extraction of trading-relevant data (capacity, yield, capital commitments). Excludes non-material commentary.

• Updated FY25 Guidance: FY25 underlying NPAT expected at lower end of analyst range ($27.0M–$34.4M), citing weak global RV sales and reduced manufacturing volumes.
  • FY26 Outlook: Opening net debt ~$500M; double-digit rental revenue growth in NZ/AU (25% higher forward bookings), but USA bookings down single-digit YoY post-seasonal recovery.
  • Potential Impairment: Preliminary NZ$36M goodwill impairment likely for USA business due to uncertain travel demand; other non-cash one-offs possible (no covenant impact).

No material capital markets actions (e.g., raising, trading halt) identified.
